    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras are positioned for a high-floor offensive day, anchored by **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (76.96) and **Colt Keith** (66.91). **Pete Crow-Armstrong** leads the field today, as a favorable matchup against R. Nelson provides the runway needed to exploit his elite speed, making him our primary target for the scarce stolen base category. Similarly, **Colt Keith** benefits from a strong lineup position and a slow-delivery opponent in Kumar Rocker, which optimizes his potential to swipe bags and drive runs. **Junior Caminero** (65.85) remains a pillar in the middle of our order; while the park factors are slightly suppressive, his matchup against Roupp is technically sound, and he continues to be a high-upside play for RBI production.\n\nThe most difficult decision for the lineup was the exclusion of **Chase Meidroth** (47.06). While **Chase Meidroth** offered a respectable floor, he ultimately sat behind **Dillon Dingler** and **Luke Raley** because those players leverage superior platoon advantages or higher-frequency opportunities to capitalize on the weak pitching staff we face today. Risks to monitor include the \"Lineup Pending\" status for **Dillon Dingler**, **Colt Keith**, **Hyeseong Kim**, **Josh Smith**, and **Luke Raley**; should any of these players drop lower in their respective batting orders, their efficiency scores will require immediate re-evaluation. Additionally, while **Yordan Alvarez** (53.88) remains a core asset, owners should exercise caution against the lefty-lefty matchup with Early, which creates a slight volatility risk despite his elite xwOBA. We continue to hold **Christian Yelich** on the IL and **Zac Veen** in the minors, waiting for improved health and availability to bolster our depth.",
